## Server Environment Variables

# Prisma database URL (e.g., Neon Postgres or SQLite)
# Postgres example:
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DB?sslmode=require"
# SQLite example for local dev:
# DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"

# Optional: OpenAI API key (symptom checker will gracefully fallback without this)
# Get a key at: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=""

# JWT secret for signing tokens (set a strong value in production)
JWT_SECRET="replace_with_strong_secret"

# Port to run the server on (defaults to 4000)
PORT=4000

# Comma-separated list of allowed CORS origins
# Example: http://localhost:5173,https://your-frontend.example.com
CORS_ORIGIN=""

# Admin email to treat as ADMIN on login
ADMIN_EMAIL="admin@telmed.com"

## Instructions
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Replace placeholder values with actual credentials
# 3. For local dev without Postgres, you can switch to SQLite by updating prisma/schema.prisma provider and DATABASE_URL
